This includes an audio edit using @SternGeek's source.

This audio has been dyson compressed at 80% and amplified for minimum range. It
has a small amount of white noise mixed in to the final render to get rid of
those awkward silences that the MP3 format sometimes creates when there's not
enough volume to compress. Talk Radio & Podcasts sound much better, especially
thru earbuds, with this edit. You will also find it easier to hear audio details
in loud environments. If you have good speakers, or listen in a quite
environment, you don't need this. This encode should also use considerable less
power from your batteries
